JOHANNESBURG - Former acting Hawks head, Berning Ntlemeza, is heading to the Supreme Court of Appeal.The North Gauteng High Court last week ordered Ntlemeza to vacate his position, describing his appointment as unlawful.Police Minister, Fikile Mbalula, then appointed Yolisa Matakata as acting Hawks head.Ntlemeza was expected to pitch at the office today, but his lawyer says he'll only be back at his desk on Monday.READ: Ntlemeza to defy Mbalula and report for dutyeNCA